        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Periodontal pain attributed to apical periodontitis due to endodontic disease because of partial or total pulp necrosis and endodontic infection that have been diagnosed by: non-vital pulp, evidenced by either: direct inspection, or non-response to pulp vitality testing or a previously debrided root canal or clinical or radiographic evidence of apical inflammation.</obo:IAO_0000115>
